Per-Leg Stop Loss
In order for the per-leg stop loss choice to appear, you first need to enter a value into the stop loss field.

This option will cause the trade to be closed on stop loss, based on an individual selected leg– not the whole spread.

Note: This is a niche option, and should only be used if you have a specific use case. It is off by default.


Use Profit Actions

Profit actions allows you to scale out of a percentage of each trade at certain profit targets, adjust your stop loss, or both!

Any remaining allocation will fall back to the main PT/SL parameters (if specified) and/or remaining exit conditions.
The trade log will show each time a partial profit is taken as well as the quantity closed
